    "p": [
      "Protect session IDs set up via the use of cookies.",
      "Protecting session IDs helps protect user sessions from being hijacked.",
      "To protect session IDs:",
      "Store session IDs in cookies. This is the default behavior in most Scala applications. Cookies have to be turned on for this to work.",
      "Set the \"secure\" flag on session cookies. This is the default behavior in most Scala  applications. SSL has to be turned on for this to work. Enable the Secure flag on the cookie using “application.session.secure=true” in the “application.conf” file.",
      "Set the \"HTTPOnly\" flag on session cookies. Enable the HTTPOnly flag using “application.session.httpOnly=true” in the “application.conf” file.",
      "Do not disclose session IDs. Make sure that session IDs are not disclosed in URLs, logs, or error messages. Do not allow URL rewriting of session cookies."
